1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,600
Every banana emits a tiny bit of radiation — and that is completely normal.

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:09,200
What you’re tasting is potassium-40, a naturally occurring isotope.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:10,400
Yes, it's radioactive.

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,600
But don’t worry!

5
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:15,200
The levels are tiny — so tiny, they're harmless.

6
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:21,600
In fact, you’d need to eat about 10,000 bananas in one sitting to feel any effect!

7
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:27,600
That’s why scientists developed the 'banana equivalent dose' — a fun way to measure radiation!

8
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:31,200
Remember, everything around us has some level of radioactivity.

9
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,400
It’s perfectly natural.

10
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:36,400
Next time you enjoy a banana, appreciate its unique quirks!

11
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:39,200
Like and follow for more weird science!
